Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless spectrum sensing network and modulation classification problem, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new data-driven model for automatic modulation classification based on long short term memory (LSTM), which is a type of deep learning model. Hence, it is likely to belong to the machine learning sub-category.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with signal classification and modulation schemes, which are related to information theory.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a deep learning model for signal classification, which is a sub-field of artificial intelligence.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with distributed wireless spectrum sensing network, which involves control and management of systems. Hence, it is likely to belong to the systems and control sub-category.
